<h3></h3>
<div class='layout'><p>6 Rescue</p><p>第6章 拯救</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>LEGGEN, JENARR:……His contributions to meteorology, however, although considerable, pale before what……ever since been known as……Leggen Controversy. That……actions helped to place Hari Seldon in jeopardy is undisputable,……argument rages--and……always raged--as to whether those actions were……result of unintentional circumstance or part of a deliberate conspiracy. Passions have been raised on both sides……even……most elaborate studies have come to no definite conclusions. Nevertheless,……suspicions that were raised helped poison Leggens career……private life in……years that followed……</p><p>杰纳尔·雷根：……他在气象学上虽颇有贡献，但与所谓的“雷根悬案”相较之下，那些贡献尽皆黯然失色。他的行动曾将哈里·谢顿置于险境，这已是不争的事实。不过引起众人争论……而且始终争论不休的……在于这些行动究竟是无意间导致的结果，抑或是蓄意阴谋的一部分。双方争得面红耳赤，但即使最深入的研究也无法得出定论。无论如何，在其后数年间，光是涉嫌便几乎毁掉雷根的事业与私生活……</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>ENCYCLOPEDIA GALACTICA</p><p>……《银河百科全书》</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>It……not quite……end of daylight when Dors Venabili sought……Jenarr Leggen. He answered……rather anxious greeting with a grunt……a brief nod. </p><p>当铎丝·凡纳比里找到杰纳尔·雷根的时候，白昼时光尚未完全结束。对于她带着焦虑的问候，他的回应是哼了一声，并随便点了点头。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Well,……said a trifle impatiently. "How……he?"</p><p>“好，”她带点不耐烦地说，“他怎么样了？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Leggen,……was entering data into……computer, said, "How……who?"</p><p>雷根一面将资料输入电脑，一面说：“谁怎么样了？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"My library student Hari.……Hari Seldon. He went up with you.……he……help to you?"</p><p>“我的图馆课学生哈里，哈里·谢顿博士。你今天带他到上面去，他对你有没有什么帮助？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Leggen removed……hands from……keys of……computer……swivelled about. "That Heliconian fellow? He……of no……at all. Showed no interest whatever. He kept looking at……scenery when there……no scenery to look……A real oddball.……did……want to send……up?"</p><p>雷根将双手从电脑键盘上移开，转过身来。“那个赫利肯佬？他一点用都没有，也没表现出任何兴趣。他一直在看风景，其实根本没什么风景可看。真是个怪人，你为什么要让他上去？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It wasn't my idea. He wanted……I can't understand……He……very interested. Where is he now?"</p><p>“那不是我的主意，是他自己想去的。我无法了解，但他的确非常有兴趣……现在他在哪里？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Leggen shrugged. "How would I know? Somewhere around."</p><p>雷根耸了耸肩。“我怎么会知道？在附近吧。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Where……he go after he came down with you?……he say?"</p><p>“跟你们下来之后，他到哪里去了？他有没有说？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"He didnt come down with……I told……he wasnt interested."</p><p>“他没有跟我们一起下来。我跟你说过，他没兴趣。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Then when……he come down?"</p><p>“那么，他是什么时候下来的？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I don't know. I wasnt watching him. I……an enormous amount of work to……There must have been a windstorm……some sort of downpour about……days……and neither……expected. Nothing……instruments showed offered a good explanation……it or……the fact that some sunshine we were expecting today didnt appear.……Im trying to make sense of it……youre bothering me."</p><p>“我不知道。我没看着他，我有一大堆事要做。大约两天前，一定曾有一场风暴和某种豪雨，两者都是始料未及的。我们预期今天会出现的阳光，却又偏偏不肯露脸。我们的仪器所显示的数据，对这些现象都无法提出一个好的解释。现在我正试图弄明白，而你却在打扰我。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You mean……didnt……him go down?"</p><p>“你的意思是，你没看到他下来？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Look. He wasnt on my mind.……idiot wasnt correctly dressed……I could……that inside of half an hour he wasnt going to be able to take……cold. I gave……a sweater,……that wasnt going to help much……his legs……feet. So I left……elevator open……him……I told……how to……it……explained that it would take……down……then return automatically. It……all very simple……Im sure he……get cold……he……go down……the elevator……come back……then eventually we……went down."</p><p>“听着，我根本未曾想到他。那个白痴没穿对衣服，我看得出来，不到半小时他就会受不了上面的寒冷。我给了他一件毛衣，那对他的腿和脚却没什么帮助。所以我让升降机开着，并且告诉他如何使用；我对他解释，说升降机把他带下去之后，会自动回到上面来。整个程序非常简单，我确定他果真耐不住寒冷，果真提早离去，然后升降机又回到上面，最后我们也都下来了。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But……don't know exactly when he went down?"</p><p>“可是，你不晓得他究竟何时下来的？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No, I don't. I told you. I……busy. He certainly wasnt up there when we left, though,……by that time twilight……coming on……it looked as though it might sleet. So he……to have gone down."</p><p>“对，我不知道。我告诉过你，当时我很忙。不过我们离开时，他的确不在那里。而且那时暮色即将降临，看来好像还要下冰珠。所以他必定早就离开了。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Did anyone else……him go down?"</p><p>“有没有任何人看到他下来？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I don't know. Clowzia……have.……was with……for a while.……don't……ask her?"</p><p>“我不知道。克劳吉雅也许看到了，她曾经跟他在一起一会儿。你为何不去问她？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors found Clowzia in……quarters, just emerging from a……shower.</p><p>铎丝在克劳吉雅的寝室找到她，她刚冲完一个热水浴。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It……cold up there,"……said.</p><p>“上面可真冷。”她说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "Were……with Hari Seldon Upperside?"</p><p>铎丝问道：“在上方的时候，你和哈里·谢顿在一起吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Clowzia said, eyebrows lifting, "Yes,……a while. He wanted to wander about……ask questions about……vegetation up there.……a sharp fellow, Dors. Everything seemed to interest him, so I told……what I could tI'll Leggen called me back. He……in……of……knock-your-head-off tempers.……weather wasnt working……he--"</p><p>克劳吉雅扬起眉毛，答道：“是的，有一阵子。他想要到处走走，还问了些有关该处植物的问题。铎丝，他是个心思敏锐的人。万事万物似乎都会引起他的兴趣，所以我尽量把知道的全告诉他，直到雷根把我叫回去为止。雷根当时脾气坏得想杀人，天气并不理想，而他……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors interrupted. "Then……didnt……Hari go down in……elevator?"</p><p>铎丝插嘴道：“那么，你没有看到哈里搭升降机下来？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I didnt……him at……after Leggen called me over.--But he……to be down here. He wasnt up there when we left."</p><p>“雷根把我叫回去之后，我就再也没有看到他……不过他一定下来了，我们离开的时候，他已经不在上面。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But I can't find……anywhere."</p><p>“可是我到处都找不到他。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Clowzia looked perturbed. "Really?--But……got to be somewhere down here."</p><p>克劳吉雅看来也慌了。“真的？可是他一定在下面。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No, he doesnt have to be somewhere down here," said Dors,……anxiety growing. "What if……still up there?"</p><p>“不，他并不一定在下面。”铎丝越来越焦急，“万一他还在上面呢？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Thats impossible. He wasnt. Naturally, we looked about……him before we left. Leggen……shown……how to go down. He wasnt properly dressed……it……rotten weather. Leggen told……if he……cold……to wait……us. He……getting cold. I know! So what else could he do……go down?"</p><p>“那是不可能的，他绝不在上面。离开之前，我们自然到处找了找。雷根曾教他怎么下来。他的衣服不够，而且当时天气很糟。雷根告诉他，觉得冷的话就不必等我们。那时他已经开始冷了，我知道！所以除了下来之外，他还会做什么呢？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But no……saw……go down.--Did anything go wrong with……up there?"</p><p>“可是没有人亲眼看到他下来……他在上面有没有出什么问题？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Nothing.……while I……with him. He……perfectly fine except that he……to be cold, of course."</p><p>“绝对没有，至少我和他在一起的时候没有。他好得很……当然，不过一定觉得冷。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors, by……quite unsettled, said, "Since no……saw……go down, he might still be up there. Shouldnt we go up……look?"</p><p>铎丝此时心乱如麻，又说：“既然没有人看到他下来，他就可能还在上面。我们不该上去看看吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Clowzia said nervously, "I told……we looked around before we went down. It……still quite light……he……nowhere in sight."</p><p>克劳吉雅紧张兮兮地说：“我告诉过你，我们下来之前到处找过了。当时还相当明亮，但谁也没见到他的踪影。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Lets look anyway."</p><p>“我们还是去看看吧。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But I can't take……up there. Im just an intern……I don't have……combination……the Upperside dome opening. Youll have to……Dr. Leggen."</p><p>“可是我无法带你上那里去。我只是个实习生，没有开启穹顶出口的密码。你得去求雷根博士。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors Venabili knew that Leggen would……willingly go Upperside now. He would have to be forced.</p><p>铎丝·凡纳比里知道雷根现在一定不愿到上方去，必须强迫他才行。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>First,……checked……library……the dining areas again. Then……called Seldons room. Finally,……went up there……signaled at……door. When Seldon……not respond,……had……floor manager open……He wasnt there.……questioned some of those who, over……last……weeks,……come to know him. No……had seen him.</p><p>首先，她又到图书馆与用餐区巡视一遍，然后再打电话到谢顿的房间。最后，她走到他的宿舍门口，按下门上的讯号钮。在确定无人应门之后，她请来该层的管理员开门，发现他果然不在里面。她还问了几个过去数周谢顿陆续结识的人，没有一个人看到过他。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Well, then,……would make Leggen take……Upperside. By now, though, it……night. He would object strenuously……how long could……spend arguing if Hari Seldon……trapped up there on a freezing night with sleet turning to snow?</p><p>好吧，她只好硬逼着雷根带她到上方去。不过现在已经入夜，他一定会极力拒绝。然而，在这个能冻死人的夜晚，冰珠眼看就要转为雪花，哈里·谢顿倘若果真困在上面，她又能浪费多少时间来和雷根争论？</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>A thought occurred to……and……rushed to……small University computer, which kept track of……doings of……students, faculty,……service staff.</p><p>她突然冒出一个念头，立刻冲到一台小型“大学电脑”前，这种电脑专门记录所有学生与教职员的最新状况。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>……fingers flew over……keys……she soon……what……wanted. </p><p>她的十指在键盘上飞舞，很快就找到她要的资料。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>There were three of them in another part of……campus.……signed……for a small glidecart to take……over……found……domicile……was looking for. Surely,……of them would be available--or findable. </p><p>有三个人可以求助，却都住在校园另一角。她召来一辆小型滑车将她载到那里，很快就找到了那栋宿舍。不用说，三人之中总该有一个在家……或起码找得到。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Fortune……with her.……first door at which……signaled……answered by a query light.……punched in……identification number, which included……department affiliation.……door opened……a plump middle-aged……stared……at her. He……obviously been washing up before dinner.……dark blond hair……askew……he……not wearing……upper garment. He said, "Sorry.……catch me at a disadvantage. What……I do……you,……Venabili?"</p><p>这回她很幸运。她按下第一个房门上的讯号钮，询问灯随即亮起。她键入自己的身份识别码，其中还包括她所隶属的学系。房门打开后，一个胖胖的中年男子好奇地盯着她。他显然正在梳洗，准备出去晚餐。他的深色金发凌乱不堪，而且上身未穿任何衣服。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p></p><p>他说：“抱歉，你来得真不是时候。凡纳比里博士，我能为你做些什么吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She said a……breathlessly, "Youre Rogen Benastra,……Chief Seismologist, aren't you?"</p><p>她带着轻微的喘息说：“你就是罗根·班纳斯楚，首席地震学家吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes."</p><p>“没错。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"This is an emergency. I must……the seismological records……Upperside……the last……hours."</p><p>“这是紧急事件，我必须看看过去几小时内上方的地震记录。”</p></div>
