<div class='layout'><p>"No. Stay on this one.……keep on going forward at fifteen-minute intervals.……person……have been left behind……may have made……way back to……instruments."</p><p>“不，就留在那里，继续以十五分钟为间隔推进。有个人也许落在后面，也许后来才回到仪器附近。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Benastra shook……head……muttered something under……breath.</p><p>班纳斯楚摇摇头，低声嘀咕了几句。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The screen shifted again……Dors said sharply, "Whats that?"……was pointing.</p><p>画面再度变换，铎丝突然指着屏幕喊道：“那是什么？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I don't know. Noise."</p><p>“我不知道，杂讯吧。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No.……periodic. Could it be a single persons footsteps?"</p><p>“不对，它是周期性的。有没有可能是单独一人的脚步？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Sure,……it could be a dozen other things too."</p><p>“当然可能，但也可能是不下十种的其他现象。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Its coming along at about……time of footsteps, isnt it?" Then, after a while,……said, "Push it forward a little."</p><p>“它的变化和步行的快慢差不多，对不对？”过了一会儿，她又说，“再推进一点。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He……and when……screen settled down……said, "aren't those unevennesses getting bigger?"</p><p>他照做了。等到画面稳定下来之后，她说：“这些凹凸不平是不是越来越大？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Possibly. We……measure them."</p><p>“有可能，我们可以测量一下。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"We don't have……You……see theyre getting bigger.……footsteps……approaching……transducer. Go forward again.……when they stop."</p><p>“不必了。你可以看出它们越来越大，代表那些脚步逐渐接近转换器。再推进些，看看它们什么时候消失。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>After a while Benastra said, "They stopped twenty or twenty-five minutes ago." Then cautiously, "Whatever they are."</p><p>又过了一会儿，班纳斯楚说：“是在二十或二十五分钟之前。”然后，他谨慎地补充了一句，“不论那是什么。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Theyre footsteps," said Dors with mountain-moving conviction. "Theres a……up there……while……and I have been fooling around here,……collapsed……hes going to freeze……die.……don't say, Whatever they are! Just call Meteorology……get me Jenarr Leggen. Life or death, I tell you.……so!"</p><p>“就是脚步。”铎丝以排山倒海的信心，斩钉截铁地说，“还有一个人在上面，当你我在这里浪费时间的时候，他已经不支倒地，马上就要冻死。不要再说‘不论那是什么’，赶紧打电话到气象学系，帮我找杰纳尔·雷根。生死攸关，我告诉你。就这么说！”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Benastra, lips quivering,……passed……stage where he could possibly resist anything this strange……passionate woman demanded. </p><p>班纳斯楚的嘴唇开始打颤，到了这个地步，他再也无法违抗这个古怪而冲动的女人所下达的任何命令。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>It took no more than three minutes to……Leggens hologram on……message platform. He……been pulled away from……dinner table. There……a napkin in……hand……a suspicious greasiness under……lower lip. </p><p>不到三分钟，雷根的全息像便出现在讯息平台。他是从餐桌上被拉下来的，手中还握着一条餐巾，嘴唇下面油腻腻的，不知道是什么东西。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>His long face……set in a fearful scowl. " Life or death? What is this?……are you?" Then……eye caught Dors,……had moved closer to Benastra so that……image would be seen on Jenarrs screen. He said, "You again. This is simple harassment."</p><p>他的长脸露出可怕的阴沉表情。“生死攸关？这是怎么回事？你是什么人？”然后他看到了铎丝，她故意凑近班纳斯楚，好让她的影像出现在杰纳尔的屏幕上。于是他说：“又是你，这简直就是骚扰。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said,……is not. I have consulted Rogen Benastra,……is Chief Seismologist at……University. After……and your party……left Upperside,……seismograph shows clear footsteps of……person still there.……my student Hari Seldon,……went up there in your care……who is now, quite certainly, lying in a collapsed stupor……may……live long.</p><p>铎丝说：“这不是骚扰。我已经咨询过罗根·班纳斯楚，他是本校的首席地震学家。在你和你的小组离开上方之后，地震仪又显示出清楚的脚步，代表还有一个人在那里。他就是我的学生哈里·谢顿，当初是你护送他上去的，如今我们相当肯定，他已经倒地昏迷不醒，可能活不了多久了。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You will, therefore, take me up there right……with whatever equipment……be necessary. If……do……do so immediately, I shall proceed to University security--to……President himself, if necessary.……way or another I'll……up there……if anything……happened to Hari because……delay……minute, I will……to it that……are hauled in……negligence, incompetence--whatever I……make stick--and will have……lose……status……be thrown……of academic life.……if……dead, of course, thats manslaughter by negligence. Or worse, since……now warned……hes dying."</p><p>“因此，你要尽快带我上去，并且带着一切必要装备。假如你不立刻照办，我就去找校方保安单位……甚至找校长本人，若有必要的话。无论如何，我总有办法上去的。若是因为你耽误了一分钟，而让哈里有什么差池，我保证会拿失职、无能，以及我能安在你身上的一切罪名，让你吃上官司，让你丧失所有的地位，并且被赶出学术圈。万一他不幸丧生，当然，那就是过失杀人。或者更严重的罪，因为我现在已警告过你，他快要死了。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Jenarr, furious, turned to Benastra. "Did……detect--"</p><p>火冒三丈的杰纳尔转向班纳斯楚。“你是否侦测到……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>But Dors……in.……told me what he detected……Ive told you. I do……intend to allow……to bulldoze……into confusion.……you coming? Now?"</p><p>铎丝却突然打断他的话。“他把侦测到的全告诉了我，而我又已经告诉你。我不准备让你把他吓得心神恍惚。你来不来？啊？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Has it occurred to……that……may be mistaken?" said Jenarr, thin-lipped.……you know what I……do to……if this is a mischievous false alarm? Loss of status works both ways."</p><p>“你有没有想到过，也许是你弄错了？”杰纳尔以刻薄的口吻说，“你知不知道，如果这是个恶作剧的假警报，我又能怎样对付你？丧失地位同样会应验在你身上。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Murder doesnt," said Dors.……ready to chance a trial……malicious mischief.……you ready to chance a trial……murder?"</p><p>“谋杀罪却不会。”铎丝说，“我可不怕你控告我恶意恶作剧，你怕不怕被控谋杀罪呢？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Jenarr reddened, perhaps more at……necessity of giving in than at……threat. "I'll come,……I'll have no mercy on you, young woman, if your student eventually turns……to have been safe within……dome these past three hours."</p><p>杰纳尔涨红了脸，主要原因或许并非受到威胁，而是他不得不向对方低头。“我会来的，不过，年轻女士，如果事实证明，在过去三个小时里，你的学生安然无事地待在穹顶内，那我可绝不会对你客气。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The three went up……elevator in an inimical silence. Leggen……eaten only part of……dinner……had left……wife at……dining area without adequate explanation. Benastra……eaten no dinner at……and……possibly disappointed some woman companion, also without adequate explanation. Dors Venabili……not eaten either……she seemed……most tense……unhappy of……three.……carried a thermal blanket……two photonic founts.</p><p>在直达上方的升降机中，三个人保持着掺杂敌意的沉默。雷根的晚餐只吃了一半，他没有做充分的解释，就将妻子独自留在用餐区。班纳斯楚根本未进晚餐，可能还令某位女伴大失所望，他同样未能做出充分解释。铎丝·凡纳比里也没有吃任何东西，而在他们三人之间，她似乎是最紧张、最闷闷不乐的一位。她带了一条热力毯，以及两个光子源。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>When they reached……entrance to Upperside, Leggen,……muscles tightening, entered……identification number……the door opened. A cold wind rushed at them……Benastra grunted. None of……three……adequately dressed,……the……men……no intention of remaining up there long.</p><p>当他们到达上方入口时，雷根紧绷着面部肌肉，将他的身份识别码一一输入，那道门随即打开。一阵冷风袭来，班纳斯楚不禁哼了一声。他们三人都穿得不够，不过两位男士并未打算在上面久留。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said tightly, "Its snowing."</p><p>铎丝以生硬的声音说：“下雪了。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Leggen said, "Its……snow.……temperatures just about at……freezing point.……not a kI'lling frost."</p><p>雷根说：“这是‘湿雪’，因为温度刚好在冰点上下。它并不是‘杀霜’。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It depends on……long……remains in……doesnt it?" said Dors. "And being soaked in melting snow won't help."</p><p>“那可不一定，要看你在这里待多久，对不对？”铎丝说，“而浸在融雪里也没什么好处。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Leggen grunted. "Well, where is he?" He stared resentfully……into utter blackness, made even worse by……light from……entrance behind him. </p><p>雷根咕哝道：“好了，他在哪里？”他忿忿地瞪着眼前全然的黑暗，由于身后入口处透出光线，能见度因而变得更差。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "Here,……Benastra, hold this blanket……me.……you,……Leggen, close……door behind……without locking it."</p><p>铎丝说：“来，班纳斯楚博士，帮我拿这条毯子。而你，雷根博士，把你身后的门关上，不过别锁起来。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Theres no automatic lock on……Do……think were foolish?"</p><p>“门上没有自动锁。你以为我们是傻瓜啊？”</p></div>
