<div class='layout'><p>"Give me……blanket,……Benastra," said Dors in a voice that……faint with relief.……flapped it open……spread it……in……snow. "Lift……onto it carefully……I'll wrap him. Then well carry……down."</p><p>“班纳斯楚博士，把毯子给我。”铎丝的声音不再那么紧张高亢了。她抖开毯子，铺到雪地上。“小心地把他抬到毯子上，我要把他裹起来，然后我们抱他下去。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>In……elevator, vapors were rising from……wrapped Seldon as……blanket warmed to blood temperature.</p><p>在升降机中，当热力毯加热到血液的温度时，裹在毯子里的谢顿开始冒出蒸汽。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "Once we have……in……room,……Leggen,……get a doctor--a good one--and……that he comes at once. If……Seldon gets through this without harm, I won't……anything,……only if he does. Remember--"</p><p>铎丝说：“等到我们把他送到他的房间，雷根博士，你马上去找医生……找个好的，并且务必请他立刻赶来。假如谢顿博士安然度过这一关，没有任何损伤，我就再也不会说什么，但一定要在这个前提之下。记住……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You neednt lecture me," said Leggen coldly. "I regret this……I will do what I can,……my only fault……in allowing this……to come Upperside in……first place."</p><p>“你不必教训我。”雷根冷冰冰地说，“我为此感到遗憾，会尽力负责到底。可是我唯一的错误，就是竟然准许此人到上方去。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The blanket stirred……a low, weak voice made itself heard. </p><p>热力毯动了一下，传出一声微小而虚弱的声音。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Benastra started,……Seldons head……cradled in……crook of……elbow. He said, "Hes trying to……something."</p><p>班纳斯楚吓了一跳，因为谢顿的头正好枕在他的臂弯。他说：“他想要说话。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "I know. He said, Whats going……"</p><p>铎丝说：“我知道，他在问‘发生了什么事？’”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She couldnt help……laugh just a little. It seemed such a normal thing to say.</p><p>她忍不住小声笑出来。他会这么说，似乎是很自然的事。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The doctor……delighted.</p><p>医生显得很开心。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Ive never seen a case of exposure," he explained. "One doesnt……exposed on Trantor."</p><p>“我从来没见过感冒症。”他解释道，“在川陀没有人会感冒。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"That……be," said Dors coldly, "and Im happy……have……chance to experience this novelty,……does it mean that……do……know……to treat……Seldon?"</p><p>“或许吧，”铎丝冷冷地说，“我很高兴你有机会体验这个新奇病例。但这是否代表你不知道如何医治谢顿博士？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The doctor, an elderly……with a bald head……a small gray mustache, bristled.……course, I……Exposure cases on……Outer Worlds……common enough--an everyday affair--and……read a great deal about them." </p><p>这位蓄着两小撇灰胡子的秃头老医生，此时突然龇牙咧嘴。“我当然知道。感冒症在外围世界相当普通，简直是家常便饭，我读过一大堆病例。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Treatment consisted in part of an antiviral serum……the……of a microwave wrapping.</p><p>治疗的方法包括注射抗病毒血清，以及使用微波包裹。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"This ought to take care of it,"……doctor said.……the Outer Worlds, they make……of much more elaborate equipment in hospitals,……we don't have that, of course, on Trantor. This is a treatment……mild cases……Im sure it will do……job."</p><p>“这样应该可以了。”医生说，“在外围世界的医院里，他们会使用精致得多的设备，不过我们川陀当然没有。这是对轻微症状的治疗法，我确定它会生效。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors thought later, as Seldon……recovering without particular injury, that it……perhaps because he……an Outworlder that he……survived so well. Dark, cold, even snow were……utterly strange to him. A Trantorian probably would have died in a similar case,……so much from physical trauma as from psychic shock.</p><p>当谢顿逐渐恢复，并未显现任何后遗症时，铎丝曾经想，这次他能大难不死，或许正是由于他是外星人士。黑暗、寒冷，甚至冰雪，对他而言都并非全然陌生。换成川陀人，处在类似情况下就有可能丧命，但主因并非生理上的创伤，而是心理上的震撼。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She……not sure of this, of course, since……herself……not a Trantorian either.</p><p>不过，她当然无法确定这一点，因为她自己也不是川陀人。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And, turning……mind away from these thoughts,……pulled up a chair near to Haris……and settled down to wait.</p><p>将这些思绪通通收起来之后，她拉过一张椅子坐到床边，开始静下心来等待。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>On……second morning Seldon stirred awake……looked up at Dors,……sat at……bedside, viewing a book-film……taking notes. </p><p>第三天早上，谢顿缓缓醒来，一眼就看到铎丝。她正坐在床沿，一面读着影视书，一面做着笔记。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>In a voice that……almost normal, Seldon said, "still here, Dors?"</p><p>谢顿以近乎正常的声音说：“铎丝，你还在这儿？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She……down……book-film. "I can't leave……alone,……I?……I don't trust anyone else."</p><p>她放下那本影视书。“我不能让你一个人在这里，对不对？而且我再也信不过别人了。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It seems to me that every time I wake……I……you. Have……been here……the time?"</p><p>“好像每次醒来的时候，我都会看到你。你一直待在这里吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Sleeping or waking, yes."</p><p>“不论是睡是醒，我都没离开。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But your classes?"</p><p>“可是你的课呢？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>I have an assistant……has taken over……a while. </p><p>“我有一个助教，暂时帮我代一下课。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors leaned over……grasped Haris hand. Noticing……embarrassment……was, after all, in bed),……removed it.</p><p>铎丝俯下身来，抓住谢顿的手。但她马上注意到他的尴尬（毕竟他躺在床上），于是又将手缩回去。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Hari, what happened? I……so frightened."</p><p>“哈里，发生了什么事？把我吓坏了。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon said, "I have a confession to make."</p><p>谢顿说：“我要招认一件事。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What is……Hari?"</p><p>“什么事，哈里？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I thought perhaps……were part of a conspiracy--"</p><p>“我曾想到或许你也参与一项阴谋……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"A conspiracy?"……said vehemently.</p><p>“一项阴谋？”她激动地说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I mean, to maneuver me Upperside where Id be outside University jurisdiction……therefore subject to being picked up by Imperial forces."</p><p>“我的意思是，把我设计到上方去，这样我就离开了大学的管辖范围，帝国军警就可以来抓我。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But Upperside isnt outside University jurisdiction. Sector jurisdiction on Trantor is from……planetary center to……sky."</p><p>“可是上方并未脱离大学的管辖范围。川陀各区的管辖范围，都是从星核一直延伸到空中。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Ah, I didnt know that.……you didnt come with me because……said……had a busy schedule and, when I……getting paranoid, I thought……were deliberately abandoning……Please forgive……Obviously, it……you……got me down from there.……anyone else care?"</p><p>“啊，我可不知道。但你并未跟我一起去，因为你说你的日程很忙。当我开始妄想时，便想到你是故意要遗弃我。请你原谅我吧。显然是你把我从那里救下来的，除了你，还有谁会关心？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"They were busy men," said Dors carefully. "They thought……had come down earlier. I mean, it……a legitimate thought."</p><p>“他们都是大忙人。”铎丝以谨慎的口吻说，“他们以为你早就下来了。我的意思是，那还算是合理的设想。”</p></div>
